4.Course Content-AWS Solutions Architect Associate:
-------------------------------------------------
1.Account and Security:
	-IAM: Identity and Access Management
	learn about: creating users, Roles, Policies, MFA
2.Compute:
	-EC2: Elastic Compute Cloud (virtual Server)
	-ELB: Elastic load balancer (Traffic Distribution)
	-EC2 Autoscaling: Scaling policy add or remove servers automatically
	-Lambda: serverless
3.Storage:
	-S3: simple storage service (object storage)
	-EBS: Elastic Block store only for EC2
	-EFS: Elastic file system (File sharing)
4.Networking:
	-VPC: virtual private cloud
	learn about: creating subnets, route tables, internet gateway, NAT
	-Cloud Front-CDN(content delivery network)
	-Route 53 (Domain registration	
5.Databases:
	-RDS(Relational database) SQL
	-DynamoDB NoSQL
6.Monitoring services:
	-Cloud trail (Tracking users activity)
	-Cloud watch (triggering alarm)
	-SNS (Simple Notification service
7.Three Tier Architecture
	-Web servers
	-App servers
	-Database servers
	
Topic 1: Account and security:
----------------------------
IAM: Identity and Access Management

What is Root user and IAM User ?

Root user:
.always used to login email adress, password and MFA
.Root user have full acccess
.Root user will create IAM user
.Root user will assign permission to IAM users and also revoke anytime
.Root user will create group for everyone


IAM user:
.user always login using link(12digit account number), username, password, MFA
.IAM user have limited permissions

Note:
AWS never ever sugggest root account for day-to-day-interactions

